<subSubSection id="209BF388FFFDCA0548EDE6BEFC79C9C1" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="683EA003FFFDCA0548EDE6BEFC79C9C1" blockId="1.[151,1436,1689,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA0548EDE6BEFE98C885" bold="true" box="[151,273,1689,1714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by having a dense, uniform puncture pattern in the paraocular and interocular areas, which decreases towards the vertex; posterior femur and tibia with brown hairs; tegula amberish (
<figureCitation id="F0BABC86FFFDCA0548E5E6C6FF6AC8CD" box="[159,227,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1534,1557]" captionTargetBox="[224,1360,223,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[198,1389,195,1511]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Colletes tzotzilis Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 1 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 2 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 3 — female paratype: dorsolateral view of mesosoma; 4 — female holotype: dorsal view of mesosoma; 5 — male allotype: S 7; 6 — male allotype: S 8; 7 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); and anterior femur with tuft of thick, brown bristles and dark hairs, which differs from the tuft of dark and plumose hairs found in 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA0549E7E721FD7FC929" authority="Cresson, 1868" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1868" box="[413,758,1797,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctipennis">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA0549E7E721FDC5C92A" box="[413,588,1798,1821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. punctipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0C10DDF2FFFDCA054A29E721FD7FC929" author="Cresson" box="[595,758,1797,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Cresson, E. (1868) Descriptions of North American bees - No. 1. Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History, 12, 165 - 171." type="journal article" year="1868">Cresson, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species lacks conspicuous apical hair bands on terga as is also the case for 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA05490EE70DFD10C975" authority="Friese, 1900" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1900" box="[372,665,1833,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugicollis">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA05490EE70DFD88C976" box="[372,513,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. rugicollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0C10DDF2FFFDCA054A70E70EFD10C975" author="Friese" box="[522,665,1833,1858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Friese, H. (1900) Neue Bienenarten Sud-America's. Entomologische Nachrichten Berlin, 26 (12), 180 - 184." type="journal article" year="1900">Friese, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054ADFE70DFC81C976" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[677,776,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jobeli">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054ADFE70DFC81C976" box="[677,776,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. jobeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054B6DE70DFBD4C976" box="[791,1117,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054B6DE70DFC36C976" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[791,959,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaliscoensis">C. jaliscoensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054BB1E70DFBD4C976" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[971,1117,1834,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigerrima">C. nigerrima</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054CEDE70DFA9FC976" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[1175,1302,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isabelae">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054CEDE70DFB23C976" box="[1175,1194,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054CC3E70EFA9FC976" box="[1209,1302,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">isabelae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated from these by having blue iridescence (
<figureCitation id="F0BABC86FFFDCA054B7EE76AFCC5C951" box="[772,844,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1534,1557]" captionTargetBox="[224,1360,223,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[198,1389,195,1511]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Colletes tzotzilis Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 1 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 2 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 3 — female paratype: dorsolateral view of mesosoma; 4 — female holotype: dorsal view of mesosoma; 5 — male allotype: S 7; 6 — male allotype: S 8; 7 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054BAEE769FBC4C952" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[980,1101,1869,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tzotzilis">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054BAEE769FC6EC952" box="[980,999,1870,1893]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054B82E76AFBC4C952" box="[1016,1101,1869,1893]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">tzotzilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other species by having vertex with shiny integument and scarce black pubescence, prothoracic spine poorly developed, scutum with small and uniform punctures, faded on anterior margin and S7, S8, and genital capsule as in 
<figureCitation id="F0BABC86FFFDCA054D5CE7B2FF21C9E6" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1534,1557]" captionTargetBox="[224,1360,223,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[198,1389,195,1511]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Colletes tzotzilis Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 1 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 2 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 3 — female paratype: dorsolateral view of mesosoma; 4 — female holotype: dorsal view of mesosoma; 5 — male allotype: S 7; 6 — male allotype: S 8; 7 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051933/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Figures 5– 7</figureCitation>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA05492DE79DFE3EC9E6" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[343,439,1977,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jobeli">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA05492DE79DFEE3C9E6" box="[343,362,1978,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA05490DE79EFE3EC9E6" box="[375,439,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">jobeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having malar area with striae of eroded appearance. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFDCA054CB1E79DFAF3C9E6" authorityName="Metz" authorityYear="1910" box="[1227,1402,1977,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054CB1E79DFB57C9E6" box="[1227,1246,1978,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFDCA054C96E79EFAF3C9E6" box="[1260,1402,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having thin and less eroded diagonal striae and deeper punctures on clypeus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="3CFEF08BFFFECA0648EDE5D9FCD4C865" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051933/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" targetBox="[224,1360,223,1501]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="683EA003FFFECA0648EDE5D9FCD4C865" blockId="2.[151,1436,1534,1618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFECA0648EDE5D9FEB2C823" bold="true" box="[151,315,1534,1557]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">FIGURES 1–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="AF81DB80FFFECA06493BE5D8FD1AC822" authority="Balboa &amp; Ayala" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[321,659,1535,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tzotzilis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFFECA06493BE5D8FE60C822" box="[321,489,1535,1557]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Colletes tzotzilis</emphasis>
Balboa &amp; Ayala
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41C6C16AFFFECA064AE0E5D8FD5AC823" box="[666,723,1535,1556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" rank="species">
