<subSubSection id="209BF388FFF8CA0048BDE0B0FB6ACE87" box="[199,1251,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="683EA003FFF8CA0048BDE0B0FB6ACE87" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" box="[199,1251,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFF8CA0048BDE0B0FEC7CE87" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet references the ethnic group Tzotzil from the Altos de 
<collectingRegion id="AA456EE1FFF8CA004C49E0B0FB04CE87" box="[1075,1165,151,176]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="209BF388FFF8CA0048BDE09BFD05CFBF" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="683EA003FFF8CA0048BDE09BFD05CFBF" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFF8CA0048BDE09BFEE9CEE2" bold="true" box="[199,352,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Distribution.</emphasis>
Pine-oak and tropical montane rain forests of 
<collectingRegion id="AA456EE1FFF8CA004B02E09BFC5CCEE2" box="[888,981,188,213]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
, suggesting its distribution may include mountains of 
<collectingRegion id="AA456EE1FFF8CA00494BE0C7FE0CCECF" box="[305,389,224,248]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
in the Chimalapas region and 
<collectingRegion id="AA456EE1FFF8CA004AA1E0F8FCBCCECF" box="[731,821,223,248]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
province (
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFF8CA004BD4E0C6FC30CECF" box="[942,953,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">s</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="0C10DDF2FFF8CA004BBDE0C7FBE3CECF" author="Morrone" box="[967,1130,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refString="Morrone, J. (2005) Hacia una sintesis biogeografica de Mexico. Revista Mexicana de Biodiversidad, 76 (2), 207 - 252." type="journal article" year="2005">Morrone 2005</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingRegion id="AA456EE1FFF8CA004CEFE0F8FA87CECF" box="[1173,1294,223,248]" country="Guatemala" name="Guatemala" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<collectingCountry id="1096E093FFF8CA004CEFE0F8FA87CECF" box="[1173,1294,223,248]" name="Guatemala" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="F0BABC86FFF8CA004D64E0F8FAF8CECF" box="[1310,1393,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 58. 57" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[514,1092,1007,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[470,1116,949,1856]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 58. 57 — Map of collecting localities for Colletes jobeli, C. isabelae, C. jaliscoensis and C. nigerrima. 58 — Map of collecting localities for C. solari, C. tzotzilis, C. chiaPensis, and C. guatemalensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051949/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5AF57C11FFF8CA0048BDE123FEB2CF2A" bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some females have a small notch on the anterior margin of clypeus and punctures on scape. Basal area of propodeum with longitudinal striae, which form pits with horizontal striae. Males may present scutum with shallower and sparse punctures on the anterior margin, mesosoma with shallower punctures on the lateral region, and metasomal terga with duller iridescence.
</paragraph>
